  "texts": [
    "Our method, InterrogateLLM, operates on the premise that language models exhibiting hallucinations produce inconsistent and incorrect responses to subsequent queries based on the hallucinated information.",
    "To identify hallucination in a generated answer, our approach involves prompting the model multiple times to reconstruct the input query using the generated answer.",
    "Subsequently, InterrogateLLM quantifies the inconsistency level between the original query and the reconstructed queries.",
    "By leveraging the observed inconsistencies, our approach effectively identifies potential instances of hallucination.",
    "When a large-language model generates a hallucination, it struggles to consistently reconstruct the original query, leading to variations in responses."
  ],
